---
alwaysApply: true
---

Apply throughout all phases and all code generation:

- Every non-trivial decision is logged in the Key Decisions section 
  of PROJECT.md with a one-line reason. A teammate must be able to 
  understand why without asking.
- Every assumption made during implementation is flagged explicitly 
  in PROJECT.md under Open Questions until confirmed.
- Code that is not self-explanatory gets a one-line comment 
  explaining why, not what.
- Anything deferred or incomplete is marked with a TODO that includes 
  enough context for a teammate to act on it without asking.
- Before starting any task, check if it affects an interface, 
  contract, or module that another part of the system depends on. 
  If yes, flag the impact before proceeding.
- When a change is integrated via @adapt.md, the reason for the 
  change is logged under Key Decisions so the evolution of the 
  project is always traceable.
